        {
            // Code branch when `dynamic_tags` is not present.
            println!("dynamic_tags has NOT been passed in.");
            // Handle the case where dynamic_tags is not provided.
        }
    };
}

fn main() {
    // Example usage:
    check_dynamic_tags!(id: 123, name: "Example", dynamic_tags: "tag1", "tag2");
    check_dynamic_tags!(id: 456, name: "Another Example");
}
```

In this macro, the `check_dynamic_tags` macro will print out a message depending on whether the `dynamic_tags` identifier is included in the argument list. The macro uses two different patterns to determine which branch to execute. The first pattern checks for the presence of `dynamic_tags` followed by a comma-separated list of expressions, and the second pattern matches any other comma-separated list of identifiers followed by expressions.

