// This is a conceptual answer, not a code snippet.
// ClassLoader in Java is a part of the JVM that is responsible for dynamically loading classes at runtime.
// It loads the bytecodes for classes into memory and converts them into a Class<?> object.
// There are different types of ClassLoaders like Bootstrap, Extension, and System (or Application) ClassLoader.
// You can also write your own custom ClassLoader by extending the java.lang.ClassLoader class.
